\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.7}{\ignorespaces Geometric consistency-based outlier rejection applied to GNSS measurements. Inlier points (green) are distributed along the estimated trajectory and satisfy pairwise distance consistency with map-frame estimates. Multipath-corrupted points (red) form a spatially compact cluster that is globally inconsistent with the rigid consensus and are therefore rejected, even though they are mutually self-consistent.}}{27}{}\protected@file@percent }
